            <div>
                <note n="1" xml:id="p3" type="codic" resp="#SPM">Space for illumination.</note>
                <note n="2" xml:id="p21" type="edit" resp="#SPM">MS <hi rend="italic">lo cuor Dio
                        crevant</hi></note>
                <note n="3" xml:id="p44" type="edit" resp="#SPM">MS <hi rend="italic"
                    >sangui</hi>; missing titulus over <hi rend="italic">i</hi></note>
                <note n="4" xml:id="p55" type="refer" resp="#SPM"> Cf. <title rend="italic"
                        >Macario</title>, "<hi>Cil le confonde li qual formò Adam</hi>," ll. 15339,
                    15346.</note>
                <note n="5" xml:id="p62" type="edit" resp="#SPM">MS <hi rend="italic">rica e
                        amant</hi>; apparent scribal error, cf. <title rend="italic"
                        >Macario</title>,<hi rend="italic">Ancora per moi sera rico e manent</hi>,"
                    ll. 14756, 14762.</note>
                <note n="6" xml:id="p64.1" type="edit" resp="#SPM">MS <hi rend="italic">vii</hi>;
                    missing minim</note>
                <note n="7" xml:id="p64.2" type="edit" resp="#SPM">MS <hi rend="italic"
                        >comadere</hi></note>
                <note n="8" xml:id="p72" type="edit" resp="#SPM">MS <hi rend="italic"
                        >tintende</hi></note>
                <note n="9" xml:id="p102" type="edit" resp="#SPM">MS <hi rend="italic">msso</hi>;
                    cf. <hi rend="italic">permesso</hi>, l. 107</note>
                <note n="10" xml:id="p111" type="ling" resp="#SPM"><hi rend="italic">Guardé</hi>,
                    example of metathesis; cf. Ludovisi 56, note 4: "<quote>Parrebbe strano ed
                        errato di trovare guradè e subito sopo al v. 115 guardè. Ma reggono
                        foneticamente ambedue le forme. Infatti nella Rivista di Fil. Romanza 11, 48
                        K. Bartsch e A. Mussafia: una poesia didattica del sec. XIII si ha il verso:
                            <hi rend="italic">bi à quelle Ke se n'à gurar</hi>, cui il Mussafia
                        appone la nota: <hi rend="italic">gurdar è ugale a guardar. il nesso gu o
                            go, in luogo di gua in sillabe atone, è proprio delle parlate latine e
                            del catalano altresì."</hi></quote>"</note>
                <note n="11" xml:id="p116" type="codic" resp="#SPM">Space for illumination.</note>
                <note n="12" xml:id="p134" type="ling" resp="#SPM"><hi>l'è</hi>, example of
                    unstressed subject pronoun; cf. Rohlfs §446</note>
                <!-- Provide more information for n=9 -->
                <note n="13" xml:id="p136" type="ling" resp="#SPM">cf. Morgan, <hi rend="italic"
                        >La Geste francor</hi>, p. 948: "<quote>docler : Not listed in any Italian
                        or Old French dictionary. It is always opposed to low places, leading to
                        believe it means either “tower”, “hill”, or some other type of raised spot.
                        [...] Since, furthermore, the form appears six times in this manuscript
                        (plus one as doclé), it seems unlikely to be an error each
                    time.</quote>”</note>
                <note n="14" xml:id="p142" type="edit" resp="#SPM">MS <hi rend="italic"
                        >conscier</hi></note>
                <note n="15" xml:id="p164" type="ling" resp="#SPM"><hi rend="italic"
                    >torment</hi>, metathesis</note>
                <note n="16" xml:id="p169" type="edit" resp="#SPM">MS <hi rend="italic">de cuor
                        luii</hi></note>
                <note n="17" xml:id="p175" type="ling" resp="#SPM"><hi rend="italic">coda</hi>,
                    lenition; the image is of wolves following closely behind the tail of the she
                    wolf in heat.</note>
                <note n="18" xml:id="p176" type="edit" resp="#SPM">MS <hi rend="italic">Quando el
                        sol sera ch'el sol s'acolega</hi></note>
                <note n="19" xml:id="p192" type="edit" resp="#scribe">The scribe appears to have
                    corrected to <hi rend="italic">tarda</hi> from <hi rend="italic"
                    >trada</hi></note>
                <note n="20" xml:id="p193" type="edit" resp="#SPM">MS <hi rend="italic"
                    >no</hi></note>
                <note n="21" xml:id="p218" type="ling" resp="#SPM"><hi rend="italic">dié</hi>,
                    altered form in rhymed position.</note>
                <note n="22" xml:id="p230" type="edit" resp="#SPM">This line appears to be missing
                    a verb. A possible resolution would be <hi rend="italic">la polver al vent
                        çitiere</hi> considering that <hi rend="italic">çitiere</hi> appears
                    frequently in this formulaic expression. In <title rend="italic">La Geste
                        francor</title>, however, <hi rend="italic">aventere</hi> does occur as an
                    infinitive verb: <hi rend="italic">Arso fo en fois, la polvere a ventere</hi>
                    (l. 15406, 15413) and <hi rend="italic">E in apreso la polvere aventer</hi> (l.
                    13541). This act would deny Huon a Christian burial since his body would not
                    enter the Earth, a fate reserved for traitors.</note>
                <note n="23" xml:id="p234" type="ling" resp="#SPM">Ludovisi proposes <hi
                        rend="italic">involussere</hi>, and notes that "<quote>involussar per
                        involgere è proprio della parlata Veneta ma specialmente del Friulano:
                        involussar, involussât, etc."</quote>"</note>
                <note n="24" xml:id="p241" type="codic" resp="#SPM">Space for illumination.</note>
                <note n="25" xml:id="p243" type="edit" resp="#SPM">MS <hi rend="italic"
                        >sanguuy</hi></note>
                <note n="26" xml:id="p325" type="codic" resp="#SPM">This page begins with a space for an illumination.</note>
                <note n="27" xml:id="p479" type="edit" resp="#scribe">Small cross written above <hi
                        rend="italic">fene</hi>to indicate that this word should be
                    disregarded.</note>
                <note n="28" xml:id="p512" type="codic" resp="#SPM">Space for illumination.</note>
                <note n="29" xml:id="p685" type="cod" resp="#SPM">Space for illumination</note>
                <note n="30" xml:id="p713" type="edit" resp="#SPM">MS <hi rend="italic">al davernia</hi></note>
                <note n="31" xml:id="p729" type="edit" resp="#SPM">MS <hi rend="italic">la ela duchessa</hi></note>
                <note n="32" xml:id="p739" type="edit" resp="#scribe">Scribal correction, <hi rend="italic">è</hi> above the line.</note>
                <note n="33" xml:id="p755" type="edit" resp="#SPM">MS <hi rend="italic">anigo</hi>; a minim is missing.</note>
                <note n="34" xml:id="p756" type="codic" resp="#SPM">Space for illumination</note>
                <note n="35" xml:id="p767" type="biblio" resp="#SPM">See Morgan, "Padua," 77.</note>
                <note n="36" xml:id="p776" type="ling" resp="#SPM"><hi rend="italic">malmant</hi>; syncopated syllables are common in Franco-Italian.</note>
                <note n="37" xml:id="p798" type="edit" resp="#SPM">MS <hi rend="italic">dirglie</hi>; name not present in Moisan; word unclear, but possible a scribal error for the common formulaic epic phrase <hi rend="italic">destrier d'Italie</hi>.</note>
                <note n="38" xml:id="p784" type="interp" resp="#SPM">The first person future here is awkward, and I interpret it as a continuation of Sanguyn's dialogue from l. 780. Could it be possible there are missing lines, or lines out of order?</note>
                <note n="38" xml:id="p830" type="interp" resp="#SPM">For ll. 829-30, note alternating past and present tenses. See INTRO LINK</note>
                <!-- Link previous note to introduction. -->
                <note n="38" xml:id="p852" type="edit" resp="#SPM">MS <hi rend="italic">trer a travache</hi></note>
                <note n="39" xml:id="p897" type="codic" resp="#SPM">Catchwords <hi rend="#italic">de mal talento</hi></note>
                <note n="40" xml:id="p907" type="edit" resp="#SPM">MS <hi rend="#italic">tuo</hi></note>
                <note n="41" xml:id="p912" type="codic" resp="#SPM">Space for illumination.</note>
                <note n="42" xml:id="p929" type="interp" resp="#SPM"><hi rend="#italic">e</hi></note>
                <note n="43" xml:id="p953" type="edit" resp="scribe">MS <hi rend="#italic">apasant</hi> with <hi rend="#italic">ri</hi> written above the <hi rend="#italic">as</hi></note>
                <note n="45" xml:id="p1019" type="edit" resp="#SPM">MS <hi rend="#italic">dito cunte</hi></note>
                <note n="46" xml:id="p1030" type="edit" resp="#SPM">MS <hi rend="#italic">E chel</hi></note>
                <note n="47" xml:id="p1044" type="edit" resp="#SPM">MS <hi rend="#italic">se presse mereveiere</hi></note>
                <note n="48" xml:id="p1052" type="edit" resp="#SPM">MS <hi rend="#italic">certanamt</hi></note>
                <note n="49" xml:id="p1057" type="ling" resp="#SPM"><hi rend="#italic">alquant</hi>; rhoticism.</note>
                <note n="50" xml:id="p1061" type="edit" rend="#SPM">The following line has been ommitted since it repeats l. 1059, <hi rend="#italic">E vene al re tuto li va contant</hi>.</note>
                <!-- Find way to insert the extra line for the diplomatic edition; .css should display the line in a different color. -->
                <note n="51" xml:id="p1062" type="interp" resp="#SPM">Read as <hi rend="#italic">de</hi> + <hi rend="#italic">i</hi></note>
                <note n="52" xml:id="p1070" type="codic" resp="#SPM">Space for illumination.</note>
                <note n="53" xml:id="p1085" type="ling" resp="#SPM">Elsewhere <hi rend="#italic">la drant</hi>; I leave as is since metathesis is frequent.</note>
                <note n="54" xml:id="p1086" type="interp" resp="#SPM"><hi rend="#italic">banc</hi>; final consonant altered for sight rhyme.</note>
                <note n="55" xml:id="p1095" type="edit" resp="#SPM">MS <hi rend="#italic">meiniça</hi>, scribal correction with the first <hi rend="#italic">i</hi> blotted out and an <hi rend="#italic">a</hi> above the second <hi rend="#italic">i</hi>.</note>
                <note n="56" xml:id="p1116" type="edit" resp="scribe">MS <hi rend="#italic">maena</hi>; scribe deletes the <hi rend="#italic">a</hi> to correct to <hi rend="#italic">mena</hi>.</note>
                <note n="57" xml:id="p1122" type="edit" resp="scribe">MS <hi rend="#italic">honir e vergonçer</hi>; scribe inserts <hi rend="#italic">mi</hi> after <hi rend="#italic">honir</hi>.</note>
                <note n="58" xml:id="p1127" type="edit" resp="scribe">MS <hi rend="#italic">Slo</hi>; scribe inserts <hi rend="#italic">io</hi>after <hi rend="#italic">S</hi>.</note>
                <note n="59" xml:id="p1128" type="edit" resp="scribe">MS <hi rend="#italic">traito</hi>.</note>
                <note n="60" xml:id="p1168.1" type="edit" resp="#SPM">MS <hi rend="#italic">la veritade la veritade</hi>.</note>
                <note n="61" xml:id="p1168.2" type="interp" resp="#SPM">Syncopated form of <hi rend="#italic">manant</hi>; see note to l. 776.</note>
                <!-- tag reference to l. 776 to make live link. -->
                <note n="62" xml:id="p1173" type="edit" resp="scribe">MS <hi rend="#italic">n?n</hi>; scribal correction with <hi rend="#italic">o</hi> written above indisctinct middle letter.</note>
            </div>
